==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|envie||lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|envie||lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|invidia||envy|lang=la}}, from {{term|invidere||to look at with malice|lang=la}} from ''in'' + ''videre'' ("on, upon" + "to look, see"). Displaced native {{etyl|enm|-}} {{term|ande|ande, onde|envy|lang=enm}} (from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|anda|anda, onda|breath, emotion, envy, hatred, grudge, dislike|lang=ang}}), {{etyl|enm|-}} {{term|nith|nithe, nith|envy, malice|lang=enm}} (from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{m|ang|nīþ||envy, hatred, malice, spite, jealousy}}).

